The Red Sand Accounts are Mafdet's high-scrutiny ledger class for volatile inland cargo and disputed provenance consignments.
The name refers to the Saltglass Reach's red sand terrain, the primary zone where the Accounts acquire distressed caravan debt.
The Red Sand Accounts began as a specialized ledger house tracking cargo moving through the Reach under contested ownership claims.
Over time, the Accounts developed an aggressive debt-acquisition model: identifying financially distressed caravans through Outrider contacts, offering emergency loans, then converting inland water-debts into maritime cargo liens enforceable at Mafdet.
A caravan operator owing three measures of water-debt to a Great Oasis court might find that debt purchased by the Accounts and converted into a percentage claim on their next shipment — payable at Mafdet, not the oasis.
This cross-jurisdictional debt conversion is the Accounts' defining practice and the source of their power within the Strandline Compact.
The Accounts are formally one of the Ledger House bloc's member institutions, giving them voting weight in Compact deliberations.
Their relationship with the Harbor Wardens is adversarial: the Accounts view harbor access control as a constraint on debt enforcement, the Wardens view the Accounts' tactics as a stability threat.
The Quay Concord considers the Accounts a persistent threat to port operational reliability.
The Shrine of the First Claw enforces Accounts-drafted oath-sealed instruments but views the Accounts' drafting practices with theological suspicion.
Red Sand Outriders stationed along the Saltglass Reach cairn system are the Accounts' primary field acquisition arm.

